reviews.review: Great conclusion. Fast paced and felt right!

Sure to please young children, but the movie is so ridiculous on so many levels I'm not sure fans interested in the more nuanced approach of the first two movies in the trilogy will enjoy. Shame to see it end on such a sour, convoluted note!
For someone who saw it from beginning in 1977 to end...beautifully done. You always want more-but what an incredible tribute to the saga.
Very entertaining overall. Much better than the Last Jedi. A few choices I would have done differently , but overall it is a fun escape back to the Star Wars galaxy.

A competent film that leaves the trilogy in good shape, albeit safe. Disney's Sequel Trilogy should have been planned out better from the start, but this felt like the best possible way to save it. I commend Abrams effort and look forward to the creativity freedom that Star Wars will now possess outside of the Skywalker saga.

This movie was everything I hoped it would be! After The Last Jedi (a movie I kind of liked but I felt had some serious issues), it was nice to see Star Wars return to form and provide a fitting end to both the Sequel Trilogy and the saga overall! It was an emotional rollercoaster for sure, and I will definitely be going to see it again at LEAST 2 more times.

If you are a FAN of Star Wars you will appreciate this film. If you are a casual fan or a critic looking to have your "expectations subverted" a la The Last Jedi, this may not be the film for you.

Cinematography was amazing, the score was incredible as always, and this was by far the best acting in the sequel trilogy. Docking it a half star for one small issue I had but other than that this movie is awesome!
great movie...some plot points could have been explained better but overall good.
